The paper deals with the analysis of functions over general fields, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and computational complexity (cs.CC). The applications of the higher-order Fourier analysis include list decoding (cs.IT), algorithmic decomposition (cs.DS), and testing (cs.CG, cs.DM). Therefore, these five sub-categories are the most likely ones for this paper.
